    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-21T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="270"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/58</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-21T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1345. Russian Embassy has to-day presented a memorandum being a draft program
                    which has been elaborated by the Russian Government <pb facs="0238" n="188"
                        xml:id="pg_188"/> and the United States military attaché, the last three
                    paragraphs of which are as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follow the last three paragraphs of the communication from the Russian
                    Embassy to the Department of State, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                        target="#pg_186">page 186</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Department assumes that this is sufficient answer to its 1288 of April 2, and
                    will therefore proceed at once to send the commission of railroad experts to
                    Russia unless hearing immediately from you to the contrary.</p>
                <p>Department still awaiting reply to its telegram of a week ago regarding the visit
                    of the other commission.<note n="1" xml:id="d270fn1">The <persName
                            corresp="#p_RE2">Root</persName> mission; see telegram No. 1315, Apr.
                        14, <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_107">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            p. 107</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
